@{
    Layout = null; // This disables the default layout, removing the header and footer
    ViewData["Title"] = "Terms Page";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>@ViewData["Title"]</title>

    <!-- Custom CSS and Tailwind CSS -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/styles.css" asp-append-version="true" />
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tailwindcss@2.2.19/dist/tailwind.min.css" rel="stylesheet">

    <!-- Montserrat Font -->
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Montserrat:wght@400;600;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">

    <style>
        body {
            font-family: 'Montserrat', sans-serif;
            background-color: #0e2b63; /* Background color */
            color: white; /* Text color for better readability */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<div class="logo-container items-center ml-12">

    <img src="/css/Images/BAtLogoWhite.png" alt="Logo" class="w-96 h-auto object-top ">
</div>
<body class="flex flex-col items-center justify-center min-h-screen px-4">

    <!-- Terms and Conditions Container -->
    <div class="bg-white text-black shadow-md rounded-lg p-6 max-w-3xl w-full">
        <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center text-blue-900 mb-4">Terms and Conditions</h1>

        <p class="mb-4">
            The entire process will be governed by the following Terms &amp; Conditions:
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">1. Participation</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            All permanent management and unionized members of BATB (barring LT) are entitled to participate.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">2. Previous Auction Winners</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Bid winners of vehicles from auctions that took place in the last two years will not be allowed to participate.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">3. Single Vehicle Bid</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Each eligible member may bid for only one vehicle. Bidding form should be submitted in full on the online platform. While filling the bidding form, you have to show your ID card, and your mobile phone must be with you.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">4. Vehicle Inspection</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            For security and fairness purposes, no outsiders are allowed to visit or inspect the vehicle.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">5. Vehicle Condition Verification</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Verification or information about vehicle condition will not be provided, and there will be no opportunity for a test drive.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">6. Result Announcement</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            On 4th December, Monday, 2024, the committee will tally the results and publish a final list of vehicles along with the highest bids received for each vehicle. The vehicles will be awarded to the highest bidders.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">7. Payment and Taxes</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Winners of the bid will have to deposit the quoted price along with applicable Income Tax (10%) and VAT (7.5%) in the bank account of "British American Tobacco Bangladesh Company Ltd." and submit the deposit slips to Corporate Finance within 7 working days from the result publication.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">8. Failure to Pay</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            If the awardee fails to pay within the timeline or refuses the vehicle, a penalty (10% for bikes) of the quoted price will be imposed and deducted from payroll through SCI. The vehicle will then be awarded to the next highest bidder.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">9. Ownership Transfer</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Once payment is made, winners will arrange for the transfer of vehicle ownership at their own cost. Required documents must be collected from Corporate Finance, and the ownership transfer must be completed within 7 working days of the deposit.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">10. Vehicle Handover</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            The vehicle will be handed over to the winner from its current location only after the ownership is transferred. BATB will not provide additional security if the vehicle is not picked up on time.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">11. Committee Rights</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            The committee reserves all rights to make decisions regarding the auction without assigning any reason.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">12. List of Vehicles</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            Below is the list of vehicles going up for auction, with a guideline to help you fill out the bidding form.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">13. Tie Breaker</h2>
        <p class="mb-4">
            In case two bidders submit the same bid amount for one vehicle, the winner will be decided by a toss. If there are more than two bidders, the winner will be decided by a lottery conducted by the auction committee.
        </p>

        @* <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Contact Us</h2>
        <p class="mb-6">
            If you have any questions or concerns about these terms, please contact us at <a href="mailto:support@batb.com" class="text-blue-600 underline">support@batb.com</a>.
        </p>
 *@
        <!-- Link to Product Catalog -->
        <div class="text-center mt-8">
            <a href="@Url.Action("ProductCatalogue", "Auction")" class="text-blue-600 underline font-semibold">View Product Catalog</a>
        </div>
    </div>

</body>
</html>
